    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-10-15T09:49:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-10-15T09:49:00-05:00" n="177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <head>177. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iran</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d177fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, POL IRAN–US. Secret; Limdis. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_ETLJ1"
                            >Eliot</persName> on October 14, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_WJP1"
                            >Walsh</persName>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_HRA2"
                            >Hare</persName>. Repeated to <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1"
                            >CINCSTRIKE</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-10-15T10:49:00-04:00">October 15, 1966, 10:49 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>66833. 1. Following summary October 12 conversation between Secretary and
                        <persName corresp="#p_AA7">Aram</persName> is <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                        >FYI</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_Noforn1">Noforn</gloss>. It is uncleared
                    and subject to amendment upon review of <gloss target="#t_memcon1"
                        >memcons</gloss>.</p>
                <p>2. Conversation was long and most cordial. Much time devoted to review current
                    status Viet Nam, Iran-Arab, Iran-Pak relations. <gloss target="#t_memcon1"
                        >Memcons</gloss> being pouched.</p>
                <p>3. Following bilateral matters discussed: <list>
                        <label>a.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_AA7">Aram</persName> said Shah pleased with
                            recently concluded military negotiations. Only remaining problem is need
                            for early delivery of aircraft as British may depart Persian Gulf before
                            aircraft scheduled arrive in 1968–69. Secretary replied that we have
                            procurement and budgetary problems resulting from war in Viet Nam but
                            that within framework our past discussions we will do our best on
                            deliveries to Iran. Secretary suggested in meantime necessary training
                            of Iranian air force personnel begin in case emergency should develop
                            requiring assistance earlier than planned.</item>
                        <label>b.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_AA7">Aram</persName> inquired about status Iran’s
                            request for <gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss>-480 wheat. While pointing
                            out US no longer has surplus Secretary assured <persName
                                corresp="#p_AA7">Aram</persName> within limits our short supply
                            there is every disposition in <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> to do
                            best we can for Iran.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
